channel.title: Interleaved RSS Feed
channel.description: This is an interleaved feed of the most recent entries from each RSS source, skipping any feeds with errors.

item.title: NEW: Arizona Legislature, RNC File Emergency Request With SCOTUS on State Law Over Voting and Illegals
Harris supporters sound off on her border blueprint: ‘Her policies will make a difference'
item.description: Attendees at Kamala Harris and Tim Walz' Arizona rally on Friday were asked to define the nominee's border policies, and offered their take on her other proposals and record.

item.title: Trump Stumps For Fmr SEAL in Montana, Rips Dem Sen. Tester
item.description: Montana might not be a battleground state for November's presidential election - Donald Trump carried it by 16.37 percentage points in 2020 and by nearly 21 in 2016 - but it sure could decide which party gains control of the Senate.

item.title: Pro-Hamas Protesters Interrupt Kamala Harris Rally Again, She Answers With Another Meaningless Word Salad
Harris addresses anti-Israel protesters at Arizona rally as crowd tries to drown them out with 'USA!' chants
item.description: Vice President Kamala Harris told anti-Israel protesters at her rally in Glendale, Arizona, on Friday that she and the president are working toward a Gaza cease-fire.

item.title: Trump: America Can't Survive 'Bumbling, Communist Lunatic'
item.description: Former President Donald Trump told a campaign rally audience in Bozeman, Montana, Friday night that the United States cannot withstand a Kamala Harris presidency.

item.title: NEW: JD Vance Crushes Kamala Press Avoidance, Then NBC Reporter's Reply Goes Over the Edge
Arizona Kamala Harris rally speakers court 'John McCain Republicans' support; man brings border map for VP
item.description: A theme among several of the speakers at Vice President Kamala Harris' campaign rally outside Phoenix Friday was courting supporters of the late moderate GOP Sen. John McCain.

item.title: Trump: Harris Won't Do Interviews Because She's 'Dumb'
item.description: Former President Donald Trump went on the offensive Friday night in Montana against Vice President Kamala Harris, calling out her lack of interviews since being elevated to the top of the Democrat ticket following President Joe Biden's decision to not seek reelection.

item.title: Harris Campaign Finally Responds to Tim Walz Stolen Valor Scandal With Pathetic Statement
Tim Walz 'misspoke' about using weapons ‘in war,' Harris campaign says: report
item.description: Minnesota Gov. Tim Walz, Kamala Harris' running mate whose military service has come under heavy scrutiny, "misspoke" in a 2018 video where he is heard talking about his handling of weapons "in war," the Harris campaign says.

item.title: Trump: Media 'Fake,' 'Nastiest People on Earth'
item.description: Former President Donald Trump continued on the campaign trail Friday night, traveling to Bozeman, Montana, where he held a campaign rally at the Brick Breeden Fieldhouse.

item.title: Feel-Good Friday: TSA Explosives Detection Dogs Get Great Retirement Send-Off Parties
US officials identify Buffalo Soldier killed in World War II
item.description: The remains U.S. Private First Class Lemuel Dent Jr. were recently identified by the DPAA, which is working to identify dozens of Buffalo Soldiers who were killed in World War II.

item.title: Caroline Sunshine to Newsmax: Kamala Harris a 'Fake Actress'
item.description: Deputy Communications Director for the Trump presidential campaign Caroline Sunshine told Newsmax on Friday that Vice President Kamala Harris is "a fake actress who will play somebody tough on stage." On Thursday, Harris spoke with reporters for the first time in almost three ...
